## `test_bench_stat_4k_hot_cache(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-bench-2 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: runtime measurement -->

### Purpose
Hot-cache stat of a small file should be ≤ 2 ms (very loose bound — real target is sub-100 µs on modern hardware; we leave headroom for slow CI).

### Postconditions

```python
path = mount / "f"
path.write_bytes(b"x" * 4096)

per_op = _measure(lambda: os.stat(path), iterations=1000)
assert per_op < 2e-3, f"stat too slow: {per_op * 1e6:.1f} us/op"
```

