## `test_bench_git_log_on_small_repo(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-bench-7 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: runtime measurement + external tool -->

### Purpose
`git log` on a modest repo inside the mount must finish within 3× ext4. We proxy with a hard wall-clock bound.

### Postconditions

```python
if not shutil.which("git"):
    pytest.skip("git not installed")

repo = mount / "repo"
repo.mkdir()

subprocess.run(["git", "-C", str(repo), "init", "--quiet"], check=True)
subprocess.run(["git", "-C", str(repo), "config", "user.email", "t@t"], check=True)
subprocess.run(["git", "-C", str(repo), "config", "user.name", "t"], check=True)

# 100 commits.
for i in range(100):
    (repo / f"f{i}.txt").write_text(f"v{i}\n")
    subprocess.run(["git", "-C", str(repo), "add", f"f{i}.txt"], check=True)
    subprocess.run(["git", "-C", str(repo), "commit", "-m", f"c{i}", "--quiet"],
                   check=True)

start = time.perf_counter()
subprocess.run(["git", "-C", str(repo), "log", "--oneline"],
               check=True, capture_output=True)
elapsed = time.perf_counter() - start
assert elapsed < 5.0, f"git log on 100-commit repo: {elapsed:.2f}s"
```

