## `test_bench_tar_create(mount, tmp_path)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-bench-9 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: runtime measurement + external tool -->

### Postconditions

```python
if not shutil.which("tar"):
    pytest.skip("tar not installed")

# 10k small files.
for i in range(10_000):
    (mount / f"f{i:05d}").write_bytes(b"x" * 100)

archive = tmp_path / "out.tar"
start = time.perf_counter()
subprocess.run(["tar", "-cf", str(archive), "-C", str(mount), "."],
               check=True)
elapsed = time.perf_counter() - start
assert elapsed < 10.0, f"tar over 10k files: {elapsed:.2f}s"
```

